Package selrach.bnetbuilder.model.variable

Class Summary
Clique A clique is a group of completely connected variables that is a subset of some variables.
CliqueSeparator A CliqueSeparator contains the intersection of two cliques.
ContinuousVariable A ContinuousVariable has a continuous range of values.
DiscreteVariable A DiscreteVariable is a variable with a limited amount of states that it can be in.
Factor Factor object, its used when we are dealing with only transient variables.
GraphVariable A GraphVariable represents a RandomVariable in the network, but its connections can be manipulated without affecting the original network.
JunctionTree Represents a junction tree slice in the dynamic network.
JunctionTreeTemplate This contains the information needed to print off more JunctionTree as the time horizon extends past the original slice.
Potential Manages a distribution over a Clique or CliqueSeparator.
RandomVariable Represents the generic commonalities between the different types of variables in the network.
TransientClique This is a short lived object that is created for a run of the junction tree.
TransientCliqueSeparator This is the transient representation of CliqueSeparators, specified for a particular time.
TransientVariable Realization variable of a template random variable for a particular time.
